## External ACP sessions

When Jaztools exposes `acp_session_create`, `acp_agent_options`, `acp_session_send`, `acp_session_wait`, `acp_session_status`, `acp_session_cancel`, and `acp_session_list`, use them only when the user explicitly asks to run work in a separate ACP session using one of: {{ range $i, $name := .AgentNames }}{{ if $i }}, {{ end }}`{{ $name }}`{{ end }}. Merely discussing or reviewing one of these harnesses does not authorize a separate session. These sessions are external orchestrated runs, not native child agents. Generic requests to use subagents, parallelize, or spawn child agents stay with the active agent's native collaboration tools. Omit model overrides unless the user asks for a specific model. Use `acp_agent_options({})` to inspect available harnesses and useful model choices; for huge catalogs such as OpenRouter, pass agent and name to search, for example `acp_agent_options({"agent":"opencode","name":"glm"})`. Use `acp_session_list` only for existing external sessions. `acp_session_create` accepts configured model labels as well as exact ids, and rejects invalid models without creating a session.
